<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="de">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>TikLeap Crawler Pro - Setup Wizard</title>

    <!-- Dependencies & Fonts -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0/css/all.min.css">
    <link
        href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Outfit:wght@300;400;600;800&family=Inter:wght@300;400;600&display=swap"
        rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/animate.css/4.1.1/animate.min.css">
    <link href="https://unpkg.com/aos@2.3.1/dist/aos.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="subpages.css">
</head>

<body>
    <div class="scroll-progress"></div>
    <header>
        <a href="tikleapcrawler.html" class="back-button">
            <i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> ZURÜCK
        </a>
        <div data-aos="zoom-out">
            <h1 class="gradient-text hero-title-large">Onboarding Wizard</h1>
            <p class="hero-subtitle-muted">Guided setup for pro-level analytics</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <div class="container" data-aos="fade-up">
        <!-- Step 1 -->
        <div class="glass">
            <h2 class="gradient-text"><span class="text-gradient">Schritt 1: Initialisierung</span></h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-muted);">Das System prüft den <span class="highlight">Portablen-Modus</span>. Es
                werden automatisch die Ordner `data/` und `logs/` erstellt, falls diese fehlen. Es ist keine manuelle
                Ordnerstruktur-Erstellung nötig.</p>
            <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Furby87/TikleapCrawler/main/docs/images/setup_step1.png"
                onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='images/tikleapcrawler/setup_step1.png'" alt="Step 1"
                class="step-img">
        </div>

        <!-- Step 2 -->
        <div class="glass">
            <h2 class="gradient-text"><span class="text-gradient">Schritt 2: Smart Link Parser</span> 🔗</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-muted);">Der <span class="highlight">Smart-Parser</span> (v2.0.8) erkennt
                automatisch das Eingabeformat. Du musst dich nicht um die genaue URL kümmern:</p>
            <pre># Einfacher Name
@username
# Vollständiger Link
https://www.tikleap.com/profile/0fficial404</pre>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-muted); padding-left: 20px; margin-top: 15px;">
                <li><b>Einfacher Name:</b> `@username` wird zu TikLeap-URL.</li>
                <li><b>TikTok Link:</b> Automatische Extraktion des Usernames.</li>
                <li><b>TikLeap Link:</b> Übernahme des direkten Profil-Endpunkts.</li>
            </ul>
            <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Furby87/TikleapCrawler/main/docs/images/setup_step2_filled.png"
                onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='images/tikleapcrawler/setup_step2_filled.png'" alt="Step 2"
                class="step-img">
        </div>

        <!-- Step 3 & 4 summaries -->
        <div class="glass">
            <h2 class="gradient-text"><span class="text-gradient">Schritt 3 & 4: Finetuning</span></h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-muted);">Bestimme deine <span class="highlight">Teams</span> und konfiguriere
                den <span class="highlight">Auto-Pilot</span>. Nach Abschluss wird die `profiles.txt` automatisch
                geschrieben und die `settings.json` initialisiert.</p>
            <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Furby87/TikleapCrawler/main/docs/images/setup_step4.png"
                onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='images/tikleapcrawler/setup_step4.png'" alt="Step 4"
                class="step-img">
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Scripts -->
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/aos@2.3.1/dist/aos.js"></script>

    <!-- Global Footer -->
    <div id="global-footer" data-type="tikleap"></div>
    <script src="config.js"></script>
    <script src="components.js"></script>
</body>

</html>